data.title: Tribute To Brummies Who Served in World War One Casualty Listing Friday 18 August 1916
data.meta_description: Tribute To Brummies Who Served In World War One Casualty Listing 	Friday 18 August 1916 - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. This document lists the names, ranks, and regiments of 61 fallen soldiers from Birmingham who died on August 18, 1916. The soldiers came from a variety of British, Indian, Australian, and Canadian regiments. Many were from the Royal Warwickshire Regiment, which was a local regiment.
